CSC280 has the course title "Computer Models and Limitations".
CSC280 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Lane Hemaspaandra.
CSC280 is offered every Fall and Spring and Summer.
 This course studies fundamental computer models and their computational limitations. Finite-state machines and pumping lemmas, the context-free languages, Turing machines, decidable and Turing-recognizable languages, undecidability, NP-completeness. Prerequisites include CSC173 and MATH150.YOU MUST REGISTER FOR A RECITATION WHEN REGISTERING FOR THE MAIN COURSE
